article.headline: E. Kentucky 44, SE Missouri 17
article.story: RICHMOND, Ky. -- Bobby Washington and Mark Dunn combined to score four rushing touchdowns as Eastern Kentucky beat Southeast Missouri 44-17 on Saturday. The Colonels (5-2, 4-0 Ohio Valley Conference) totaled 501 yards of offense and scored 24 straight points after Southeast Missouri (2-4, 0-3 OVC) went up 7-0 on a 2-yard run by Victor Anderson. Washington scored twice on 1-yard runs in the third and fourth quarter and finished with 47 yards on 18 carries. Dunn ran for 46 yards and added two scores in the first quarter. Quarterback Allan Holland threw for 361 yards and scored on a 1-yard run with 9:09 left in the second to put the Colonels up 21-7.
